				<p>@hauptmech - I agree with all of your comments. I would argue that smooth inputs (S-curves) make smooth**er** motions, but attempting to modulate the speed or position profile to explicitly avoid resonance is a form of control called input shaping. I think that, for industrial robot arms, they use compliant control over input shaping.</p>
